S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Display Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain system display settings or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only one feature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Country Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date of Last Update
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date when something was last updated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date of Issue
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: First date item was reported to IALA.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Transmitting Station ID
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: ID of transmitting station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Transmitted Message Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Transmitted message type from DGNSS station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GPS Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Primary message type which provides the differentially corrected pseudorange measurement that should be processed by the User Equipment navigation filter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Delta Differential GPS Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that is provided for situations where the user equipment may not immediately decode new satellite ephemerides in the satellite data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Reference Station Parameters
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that contains reference station information. It includes GPS coordinates (Earth-Centered-Earth-Fixed (ECEF)) of the reference station antenna to the nearest centimetre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reference Station Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that contains the reference station datum information. It is designed to inform user equipment of the datum used for the reference station coordinates in Message Type 3 or 32 associated with the corrections being broadcast by the Reference Station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Constellation Health
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that provides information that can assist in the operation of differential GPS user equipment. It is a mechanism through which the observations made at the reference station can be automatically used by the user equipment to improve performance without operator intervention.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Null Frame
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that contains no parameters and will be used as transmission fill, if required. Its purpose is to provide messages when the GPS Reference Station has no other message ready to send, or to synchronize the beginning of a message to come unspecified epoch.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: DGPS Radio Beacon Almanac
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that sends the radiobeacon almanac, which provides the location, frequency, service range, and health information for a network of marine radiobeacons equipped to transmit differential GPS data. It also provides the identification of the broadcast station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pseudolite Almanac
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that sends the pseudolite almanac. It is similar to the beacon almanac message (Message Type 7).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Partial Correction Set
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that services the same purpose as the Type 1 Message, in that it contains the primary differential GPS corrections. However, unlike Type 1's, this message does not require a complete satellite set.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: P-Code Differential Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message has been reserved for P-code users, who will want differential corrections for both L1 and L2 frequencies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: C/A-Code L1 L2 Delta Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message has been reserved for C/A-code L2 corrections in case future GPS satellites transmit the C/A code on the L2 frequency.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pseudolite Station Parameters
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message has been reserved for a Pseudolite Station Parameter message which will provide clock offset parameters and the location of the phase center of the pseudolite transmitter antenna.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ground Transmitter Parameters
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that identifies the location and estimated range of the data link transmitter transmitting the differential corrections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Time of Week
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that is a special time tag message intended to supplement the time information provided by the modified Z-count available in the message header.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ionospheric Delay Message
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that is designed to provide ionospheric delay and delay rate of change along the line of sight vector to different satellites.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Special Message
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that is a special GPS ASCII message that can be displayed on a printer, CRT, LCD or other graphic display.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GPS Ephemerides
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that contains GPS satellite ephemeris information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RTK Uncorrected Carrier Phases
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that gives Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) measurements for uncorrected carrier phases.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RTK Uncorrected Pseudo Ranges
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that gives Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) measurements for uncorrected pseudoranges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RTK Carrier Phase Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that gives Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) carrier phase corrections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RTK/Hi-Accuracy Pseudorange Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that gives Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) / High accuracy pseudorange corrections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extended Reference Station Parameters
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that provides a means of achieving sub-millimetre precision for base station coordinates in a kinematic application and base station antenna height above a monument, which enables mobile units to reference measured position to the monument directly in real time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Antenna Type Definition Record
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message the provides the information on the antenna type used on the reference station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Antenna Reference Point (ARP)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that has been introduced to replace messages 3 and 22 for Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) operations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extended Radio Beacon Almanac
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message provides the ID of the reference stations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GLONASS Corrections
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This is the primary message type which provides the pseudorange correction for any user receiver GLONASS measurement time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GLONASS Reference Station Parameters
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message contains GLONASS reference station information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GLONASS Constellation Health
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message provides information that can assist in the operation of differential user equipment. It is a mechanism through which the observations made at the reference station can be automatically used by the user equipment to improve performance without operator intervention.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GLONASS Partial Differential Correction Set
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that services the same purpose as the Type 31 Message, in that it contains the primary differential GLONASS corrections. However, unlike Type 31's, this message do not require a complete satellite set.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GLONASS Radio Beacon Almanac
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that sends the radiobeacon almanac, which provides the location, frequency, service range, and health information for a network of marine radiobeacons equipped to transmit differential GLONASS data. It also provides the identification of the broadcast station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GLONASS Special Message
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Message that is a special GLONASS ASCII message that can be displayed on a printer, CRT, LCD or other graphic display.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GNSS System Time Offset
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message is used to relate the differential corrections from different GNSS's to each other.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Proprietary Message
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message is reserved for private use by operators who wish to use their data links to communicate proprietary information to their users.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Multipurpose Usage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This message is reserved at least temporarily, for use in exploring the use of multi-purpose data links.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Station Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of the reference tide station with reference water level for tidal stream panel observations.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Station ID
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identification of reference station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radio Beacon Health
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Operational status and integrity monitoring of DGNSS station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Beacon Operational Normal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The operation of DGNSS station is normal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Integrity Monitor Operating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The integrity monitoring is not operated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Information Available
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information about DGNSS station is not available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Do Not Use This Radio Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Do not use any information from DGNSS station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nominal Range KM
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Nominal range in Km (kilometre) for the Medium frequency signal of DGNSS.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nominal Range At
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Nominal range in microvolt per metre for the Medium frequency signal of DGNSS.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Frequency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The frequency of a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Bit Rate
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Bit rate of Medium frequency from DGNSS station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial Representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates whether a pictorial representation of the feature is available.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Periodic/Intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Communication Channel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The expected input is the specific VHF-Channel. The attribute 'communication channel' encodes the various VHF-channels used for communication.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Radio Station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radio services offered by a radio station.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A radiobeacon is a radio transmitter which emits a distinctive or characteristic signal on which a bearing may be taken.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GNSS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Differential GNSS is implemented by placing a GNSS monitor receiver at a precisely known location. Instead of computing a navigation fix, the monitor determines the range error to every GNSS satellite it can track. These ranging errors are then transmitted to local users where they are applied as corrections before computing the navigation result.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Call Sign
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The designated call-sign of a station (radio station, radar station, pilot, ...).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: An active period of a single fixed event or occurrence, as the date range between discrete start and end dates.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Dates must be encoded in the format YYYYMMDD; using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY) and, optionally, 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, the values are replaced with dashes (-). The date range of a recurring event or occurrence must be encoded using periodicDateRange.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: At least one of the sub-attributes file reference or text must be populated.The sub-attribute file reference is generally used for long text strings or those that require formatting, however, there is no restriction on the type of text (except for lexical level) that can be held in files referenced by sub-attribute file reference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The active period of a recurring event or occurrence.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Textual Description
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Encodes the file name of a single external text file that contains the text in a defined language, which provides additional textual information that cannot be provided using other allowable attributes for the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Provided by
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: a pointer to a specific feature(s) for which further information is required.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Provides
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: a pointer to a specific feature(s) for which further information is required.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Supplementary Information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Additional information that is useful within the context.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: DGNSS Station Almanac
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Detailed information about a specific DGNSS station.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: DGNSS Station Region
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Approximate region where DGNSS station is located.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radio Station
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A place equipped to transmit radio waves. Such a station may be either stationary or mobile, and may also be provided with a radio receiver.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The transmission of a radio station may serve to provide mariners with a line of position (IHO Chart Specifications, M-4). The feature 'radio station' is used to encode the point of transmission of the signal.
